<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,522,1855]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,339,1717,1743]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named in honor of Michael L. Ferro (Louisiana State University, Baton Rouge), collector of the 
<typeStatus box="[437,543,1754,1780]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,522,1855]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,302,1791,1817]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Habitat.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[366,469,1792,1818]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">holotype</typeStatus>
was emergent from CWD decay class II, and the female 
<typeStatus box="[1165,1266,1792,1818]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">paratype</typeStatus>
was collected from sifted leaf litter. Both were from secondary forest in 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13136" box="[830,932,1829,1855]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13136" name="Great Smoky Mountains National Park" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">GSMNP</collectionCode>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
